log
"Usage:\n"
"\trun.js [-j | -p | -n | -a | -v | -f] [test_folder1 test_folder2 ...] -file test_folder/test_file.js \n"
"\t-j     tests only .js test cases. Default when omitted"
"\t-p     tests only packaged test cases"
"\t-n     tests only native packaged test cases"
"\t-a     tests all: -j, -p, -n"
"\t-s     silent: hides extra messages"
"\t-f     packages are created once per jx version. Use -f to force refresh them"
"\t-r     repeats given test/tests X times. This value overrides a value given in test's .json file"
"\t-nc    no cleanup - do not remove temporary folders (useful for further inspection)"
"\t-file  allows to execute test just for one js file"
""
"\texamples:"
"\t\trun.js                 - runs .js tests from all subfolders of 'test'"
"\t\trun.js jxcore          - runs .js tests for 'jxcore'"
"\t\trun.js jxcore simple   - runs .js tests for 'jxcore' and 'simple'"
"\t\trun.js -p jxcore       - compiles all ./test/jxcore/*.js files into .jx packages\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t('jxcore_package' output folder) and runs them"
"\t\trun.js -n simple       - compiles all ./test/simple/*.js files into native packages\n"
"\t\t\t\t\t('simple_package' output folder) and runs them"
